Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function. Urinalysis reveals significant proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine color/appearance, but no hematuria or signs of infection. These findings are consistent with possible diabetic nephropathy or another form of renal impairment. Further nephrological evaluation and assessment of glycemic control are recommended.
